SUMMARY: V1 was traveling south on 2 lane highway. V1 departed its lane to the left and made a hard right turn to correct. V1 rotated in a clockwise motion and reentered original travel lane, departed the road to the right, contacted a fence and rolled 4 quarter turns before coming to rest.
V1 was traveling Northbound on roadway and struck a deer head-on.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a T-intersection. V1 departed the roadway at the end.  The front of V1 struck an embankment.

V1 was negotiating a curve and traveling on the connection ramp of two major highways. Driver lost directional control of the vehicle. V1 started to rotate counter-clockwise and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound and approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound and approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was stopped westbound at the intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and moved to the north-east. The left side of V2 impacted the front of V3.
V1 was n/b on a two-lane street approaching a dead end. V1 traveled off the roadway at the dead end. The front of V1 impacted a fence and V1 came to final rest in an agricultural field.

V1 was traveling southbound at a stop sign controlled intersection attempting to make a right turn. V2 was traveling eastbound approaching the same intersection with no controls. The rear plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2.
Unit # 1 was stopped by Police. He exited the vehicle and left the vehicle in drive. The vehicle rolled forward (with no occupants) rolled off of the right side of the road and then struck a tree.

V1 was traveling Eastbound and V2 was traveling Northbound on intersecting roads. V1 traveled thru intersection at the same time as V2 and V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 then spun and it's right side contacted V2's left side.

V1 was traveling westbound in the far right lane on a seven lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling westbound in the lane to the left of V1, on a seven lane, two-way roadway.  V2 attempt to change lanes and the left side of V1 made contact with the right rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on the roadway approaching a stop sign. As both units were coming to a stop, they collided causing damage to the rear of Unit 1 and the front of unit 2

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the road to the northwest corner. The left side of V1 impacted a fire hydrant.

Vehicle # 1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling westbound on the roadway.  Vehicle #1 was in the left lane and Vehicle #2 was in the right lane. Vehicle #1 changed lanes to the right and its right side plane impacted the left side plane of Vehicle #2. Vehicle #2 was deflected to the right and its frontal plane impacted a utility pole.
Vehicle one was southbound on a highway exit ramp.  V2 was parked on the right shoulder of the ramp.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 was behind V2. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
V1 was going east and V2 was going south on an intersecting roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front end of V2 impacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling northeast when a deer entered the roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the deer.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway. V1 traveled northeast across the westbound travel lane and departed the north road edge. The left side of V1 contacted a tree.
V1 was traveling northbound on an exit ramp.  V1 departed the roadway to the right, traveling through a field, and struck an embankment with the undercarriage of V1.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were northbound on a three-lane highway.  V1 was traveling in lane 3 and V2 was traveling in lane 1.  V1 lost control due to the wet roadway and traveled into lane 1.  The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  V2 departed the roadway to the right and entered a clockwise yaw.  V2 rolled over one quarter turn to the left.  The top plane of V2 impacted a tree, where it came to rest.
V1 was approaching sign controlled 3-legged intersection. V1 departed the roadway straight and contacted a guardrail with its frontal plane.
V1 was traveling northbound on roadway, V2 was traveling southbound on same roadway.  V1 departed the lane left and rotated counterclockwise.  The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound and approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
Vehicle 1 was southbound on a highway when it departed the right (west) side of the roadway in a clockwise rotation. The left side of vehicle one impacted a tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound in the second of four lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in the same lane behind V1. The front of V2 impacted the back of V1. After impact V2 traveled northeast across lanes three and four. The front of V2 contacted a concrete barrier.
V1 was westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed his lane on the left to avoid a NC vehicle. V1 then departed the roadway on the left and struck a tree.

V1 was traveling southbound on roadway when it hit a slick spot on the road. V1 lost control of the vehicle causing V1 to exit the roadway to the left. V1 overturned into the ditch where it came to final rest on its left side.
V2 was parked facing southbound on a residential street.  V1 was traveling northbound on the same roadway, attempting to make a U-turn.  The front of V1 contacted the back for V2.

V1 had stopped at a stop sign, heading east on a road that was leaving a business complex. As V1 was crossing over the two northbound lanes, the front of V2, which was northbound, contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling E/B on a rural roadway with traffic in both directions. While negotiating a curve to the right V1 departed the roadway and rolled down an hillside coming to final rest on its wheels on the lawn of a private residence.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  V2 was traveling southbound also on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2.

V1 was east bound on a two lane non divided roadway. V1 attempted to make a left hand turn and exited the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted into a ditch/embankment on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane three on a divided roadway when a non-contact vehicle also traveling south swerved into the lane of V1 causing V1 to depart the left side of the roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the concrete median barrier.
Vehicle #1 was traveling South.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the right.  The front plane of V1 contacted a fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southbound in the center lane of a one-way, three-lane roadway and approaching a four-leg intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling westbound in lane No. 2 of an undivided, five-lane roadway and approaching the same intersection. Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 entered the intersection, traveling on crossing paths. The front of Vehicle #1 impacted the right side of Vehicle #2 (Event 1). Vehicle #2 continued forward and impacted a "Keep Right of Median" warning sign with its left fender (Event 2).

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way two lane road.  V1 rotated in a clockwise direction and departed the roadway on the right.  The left side of V1 came into contact with concrete debris off the roadway.  V1 continued to rotate and its left side then came into contact with a tree stump.  V1 continued to rotate.  The back end of V1 then came into contact with another tree stump.

V1 was traveling through the right hand curve of the roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left, then entered a concrete drainage culvert.  The front of V1 came into contact with the wall on the opposite side of the culvert.

Vehicle 1 was stopped at an intersection facing south. Vehicle 2 was westbound in the number one lane.  Both vehicles entered the intersection, with Vehicle 1 initiating a left turn.  The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the left side of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway that was ice covered. V1 swerved to miss a non-contact vehicle that was exiting a driveway and began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the roadway to the right contacting a tree with its left side.

V1 was traveling north approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling east bound at the same traffic signal controlled intersection in the left turn lane waiting for a green arrow. V1 contacted the front plane of V2 then left the scene.

Vehicle #1 was westbound on a four-lane road approaching an intersecting roadway. Vehicle #1 initiated a right turn at the intersection and departed the left side of the road where its front end impacted a traffic signal pole (event 1). Subsequently, the pole fell onto the roof top (event 2).

Vehicle #1 was stopped, heading northwest, at an intersection and Vehicle #2 was stopped, behind V1. Vehicle #3 was approaching the intersection, decelerating. The front of V3 impacted the back of V2, then the front of V2 impacted the back of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on an undivided, two-lane roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling southbound. The driver of Vehicle #1 entered the southbound lane as she passed two police vehicles that were involved in a traffic stop. The front of Vehicle #1 impacted the front of Vehicle #2.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane two of a controlled access roadway when it contacted icy roadways and exited the road to the left. V1 traveled off the roadway into a grassy median where V1’s front and left side contacted a cable guardrail. V1 continued to travel south in the median before re-entering the roadway, where it crossed both lanes of traffic before exited the roadway on the right side. V1’s right plane contacted a metal guardrail before coming to final rest off the roadway on the right-side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two-lane, undivided roadway, approaching a three-leg intersection. The driver lost control due to icy roadway conditions and Vehicle #1 departed the left side of the roadway, impacting a ditch with its frontal plane (Event 1) and its right side plane (Event 2). The right side of the front fascia and right front wheel/tire impacted a concrete culvert (Event 3), before coming to rest.
Vehicle 1 was southbound in lane three on a highway divided by a cable guardrail.  V1 went off the left side of the road and the front and left side of V1 struck the median cable barrier.
V1 was traveling east on a highway. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same highway. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
V1 was turning left from a stopped position. V2 was crossing through the intersection. V1 (front left corner) collided with V2 (right front corner).
V2 was heading southbound. V1 was turning left from a stop sign. V1 (left front corner) collided with V2 (right front corner) in the center of the intersection.
V1 was traveling southbound in an alleyway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound on a roadway approaching the same intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle one was traveling north bound. Vehicle two was traveling south bound. Vehicle one lost control of the vehicle and impacted the front bumper on the guard rail facing and proceeded north impacting the front bumper again on the front bumper on vehicle two.
V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 started to slide sideways down the roadway. V1 departed the right lane and struck the curb off the left side of the roadway.
V1 was headed northeast on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was southbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 turned left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was attempting to cross at an intersection that had a stop sign. V1 pulled onto intersecting roadway and V1's right side contacted V2's front
The front of Vehicle #1 traveling northbound on a two lane roadway struck a tree on the right side of lane one.

V1 was traveling east on a two way undivided roadway. V1 traveled southeast and departed the south road edge. The right front wheel of V1 contacted the south road edge curb. V1 continued to travel east and the front of V1 contacted a pole.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching a 4 way intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on the same two-way, two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  V1 attempted to make a left turn to travel west when the front of V1 made contact with the front of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling westbound behind Vehicle #1. The driver of Vehicle#1 initiated a "U-turn" maneuver as the front of Vehicle #2 impacted the rear plane of Vehicle #1.

V1 was traveling southbound in the left hand lane of a two-lane roadway. The vehicle left the roadway to the left, overcorrected to the right causing the vehicle to lose control as it re-entered the roadway, the vehicle was in a CW rotation as it crossed the right-hand lane and left the roadway to the right where it struck four trees before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling westbound approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling northbound approaching the same traffic signal controlled intersection. The left plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2.

V1 was attempting to make a left turn at a crossover intersection for the divided one way highway. V2 was traveling on the crossing highway for V1’s crossover intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling northbound when it departed the left road edge into the median. The front plane contacted three metal cable guardrail support posts.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two approaching a four legged intersection V2 was traveling northbound in lane two approaching the same intersection. V1's left side contacted V2's front in the middle of the intersection, causing V1 to continue to travel northwest off the road where the front contacted a utility pole before coming to final rest, while V2 came to final rest slightly past the first impact, in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound negotiating a curve on a 2 lane, 2-way, undivided roadway. V1 began to hydroplane on the wet roadway, rotated counter-clockwise, departed the road to the right and rolled right 2 quarter turns.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North on a bridge. V1 hit a puddle and lost control. V1 departed the road to the left and the front end contacted a curb. V1 re-entered the road and departed it again to the right, and the front plane contacted a metal guardrail.
Southbound V1 lost control on an icy two-lane,two-way road, departed the right-hand side of the road, and came to rest in a ditch.

Southbound V1 lost control on an icy two-lane, two-way road and entered a clockwise rotation.  V1 crossed into the northbound lane and left side of V1 impacted the northbound guardrail.  V1 then continued back across the roadway where front of V1 impacted the southbound guardrail.  V1 came to rest facing north in the southbound lane.
V3 was stopped at a stop sign on a two lane two way road. V2 was stopped behind on the road behind V3. V1 was Eastbound on this road and collided into back of V2 which impacted the rear of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound and approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound and approaching the same intersection to turn left. Within the intersection the front of V2 impacted the left side of V2.

V1, V2, V3 & V4 were traveling westbound in lane 4 of a physically divided roadway.  Vehicles 1, 2 & 3 decelerated due to stopped traffic.  V4’s front contacted the back of V3, then the front of V3 contacted the back of V2 and then the front of V2 contacted the back of V4.

V1 was traveling N/B on a public roadway and collided with V2 turning left going S/B on that same public roadway. When V1 collided with V2, V2 then collided with V3 also turning left going S/B on that same public roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of a curved left, two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V1 departed the roadway to the right side where the frontal plane of V1 impacted two wooden utility poles located on the southern curb.  V1 then impacted its right side plane into a wooden utility support line located near the utility poles.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.  This caused the frontal plane of V2 to impact the rear plane of V3.
Vehicle #1 was stopped facing North.  Vehicle #2 was traveling North in the same lane.  The front plane of V2 contacted the back plane of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling South.  V1 lost control and began to rotate clockwise.  V1 departed the road and rolled over 4 quarter-turns to the left.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left into the eastbound lanes of traffic. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was negotiating a right hand curve on a two lane rural road with traffic in both directions. V1 departed the roadway to the left while rotating clockwise and the left side of V1 collided with an embankment causing V1 to begin to rotate counter-clockwise. The front of V1 contacted a barbed wire fence and the overturned 6 quarter turns right side leading. V1 came to final rest on its roof.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the #1 lane when traffic slowed in front.  Vehicle 1 was steered right to avoid collision with non-contact vehicle in front. Vehicle 1 departed the right road edge and drove into a one meter deep cement ditch containing 1/3 meter of water impacting its front plane.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the #4 lane and Vehicle 2 was eastbound in the #5 lane when the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2.  Both vehicles then departed the roadway on the left, into the median where the front end of Vehicle 1 contacted the cable barrier and the left side of Vehicle 2 contacted the cable barrier.
V1 passed a car on the right and cut back left in front of car. V1's front contacted v2's right side   V2 then rotated clockwise on the roadway.  The back of V2 impacted the right side of V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in an unknown lane of a roadway divided by a curbed median.  V1 passed through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the curbed median. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the northwest corner.
V1 was traveling Westbound on a two lane two way road. V1 drove onto the right shoulder of the road, lost control and slid into the roadside ditch.

v1 was travelling directly behind V2 through an interchange on to the interstate. V2 moved to the left lane and V1 did as well. V1's front then contacted V2's rear. Then V1 traveled off the roadway and V1's front contacted a light pole.
V1 was southbound on a three-lane roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and struck a utility pole with the front of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling west on a connector ramp of a major interchange. V2 was parked and occupied on the right shoulder of the same roadway. V1 drove off the roadway in an attempt to pass a semi-truck driving ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.
V2 was southbound towards an intersection.  V1 was stopped facing south at the same intersection.  The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.

V1 heading eastbound on a 4 lane roadway entering into an intersection to make a left turn. V2 heading westbound approaching the same intersection to continue westbound. V1's Left front impacted with V2's left front.

Vehicle two was traveling east bound. Vehicle one was north bound stopped at a stop sign. Vehicle one proceeded through the intersection and impacted the front bumper on the back passenger quarter panel of vehicle two.
V1 and V2 were heading southbound on a 4 lane roadway.  V1 (right) merged into Lane 1 and collided with V2 (left front).

Vehicle one was traveling south bound and lost control because the road conditions were icy. Vehicle one departed the roadway on the left side and rolled one quarter turn and came to final rest on the passenger side of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling northbound on a one-way, one lane roadway.  V1 exited the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 made contact with a utility pole.  V1 returned to the roadway, coming to final rest facing eastbound.

V2 was traveling northbound on a two-way undivided roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection.  V1 was traveling westbound in lane 2 of a two-way undivided roadway, attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling northbound on roadway. V1 left roadway on right side and traveled across field striking tree branches and a tree. V1 came to final rest in a pond.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane roadway  V1 crossed over the southbound lane,departed the roadway to the left and entered into a ditch where its front plane contacted a dirt embankment.  V1 came to rest in a yard.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, divided roadway approaching a light controlled intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a three lane, two way road way approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 an V2 were traveling westbound on a six lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a six lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling eastbound on a seven lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  V1 turned left at the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V2 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, two way roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle #1 and #3 were traveling North. Vehicle #2 was traveling South. V3 slowed for traffic, and V1 braked and turned left. V1 departed the road to the left. The right plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. The front plane of V2 then contacted the left plane of V3.
Southbound V1 lost control on icy roadway, departed right side of the roadway, and came to rest straddling the roadside ditch, with impacts to both front and back bumpers.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway.  V1 lost control due to icy road conditions and departed the roadway to the left in a counterclockwise rotation, entered a ditch and rolled right 2 quarter turns.

Driving North-bound on a 2 lane divided highway. Windy day with blowing snow. Vehicle lost traction drifted off the right side of the road, rolled to the right 2 quarter turns coming to rest on its top.

V1 departed the roadway to the right side where it contacted a guardrail. V1 continued on crossing over two lanes of travel for Southbound vehicles, a median, and two lanes of travel for Northbound traffic. V1 came to final rest on the East side of the Northbound roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling West, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound and lost directional control of the vehicle. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound approaching V1. V1 departed it's lane of travel on the left side and crossed into the same lane as V2. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound and departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 contacted a tree, began to rotate clockwise and returned to the roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound and approaching V1. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound approaching the same intersection.  V1 entered the intersection making a left hand turn.  In the intersection, the front of V1 came into contact with the right side of V2.  V2 continued in a northwesterly direction and departed the road on the left, where its front wheels/tires came into contact with the curb.  V2 continued in a northwesterly direction on the roadside until its front end came into contact with a tree.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 4-lane undivided roadway, attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway, attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V2 traveling in front of V1 braked for unknown vehicle attempting to enter the median for left turn. V1's frontal plane made contact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound, departing the roadway to its left, crossing the median and entered the southbound lanes of traffic. V1 then left the roadway to the right, crossing the median again, entering the northbound traffic lanes, crossing over both lanes before it departed the roadway to the right, striking two trees. The vehicle then caught fire.

V2 was traveling North bound approaching an exit ramp. V1 was traveling North bound in the same lane.behind V2. V2 Departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V2 struck an impact attenuater.  V2 returned to the roadway and then left side of V2 was impacted by the front of V1.
V1 traveling west departed roadway right impacted a tree and pole simultaneously. Vehicle came to rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling eastbound approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling westbound approaching the same traffic signal controlled intersection. The right plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2.

V1 was West bound on a two lane city street. The street was snow/ice covered and rutted. V1 lost control and began a counter-clockwise rotation. The right side front of V1 struck the front left corner of V2. Then the back right side of V1 contacted the back left side of V2.
V1 departed the left side of the roadway and the front of V1 struck a tree.
V1 was traveling E/B on a public roadway behind V2 and V3. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2. The collision with V1 caused the front of V2 to collide with rear of V3.

V1 was traveling on a rural-forestry road, two lane, non divided dirt road. As V1 rounded a corner in the road opperator saw a large tree across the roadway blocking both lanes of travel. Operator attempted to stop, but due to ice conditions and a down hill grade, he was unable to steer to avoid, or stop prior to impact. V1 impacted the log on the frontal plane, where it came to finial rest.

V1 was traveling east bound on a non-divided two lane, non-lined rural road. V1 departed the roadway to the right traveling approximately 200 feet before impacting a tree with its frontal plane. V1 then rotated counter clockwise, sliding down the embankment, where it impacted with a log on the right rear corner (rear plane) and a second tree on the rear plane before coming to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling West.  Vehicle #2 was legally parked facing West on the same roadway.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the right.  The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling Southwest.  Vehicle #2 was traveling Northeast on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn left at the intersection and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound in the #1 lane when the driver fell asleep and the vehicle drifted left over all lane lines, departed the curb edge and with its front bumper plane, contacted a 40 cm diameter tree.

Vehicle 1 is heading northbound in the #4 lane and begins to make a left turn into the intersection. Vehicle 2 is moving southbound in the #1 lane and the front of V2 makes contact with the front of vehicle 1. The impact forces vehicles 1 and 2 to the southwestern corner of the intersection. The left mid door of vehicle 2 made contact with a hydrant and the right front tire of V2 made contact with a wall.

Vehicle 2 was stopped in the #2 southbound lane at the intersection for a red light.  Vehicle 1 was southbound in the #2 lane when the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2.  The impact pushed Vehicle 2 forward into the crosswalk.
V1 and V2 were both in the same lane of a three-lane divided roadway. V2 was stopped ahead of V1.  The front end of V1 struck the back end of V2.
V1 was traveling S/B on a public roadway behind V2 also traveling S/B on that same public roadway. The front of V1 collided with V2's rear end.
Vehicles 1 and 2 were westbound in the #2 lane when the front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 had an trailer in tow at the time of the crash.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with one lane of travel in each direction attempting to turn left heading northbound.  V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound in the left lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction with left turn lanes on each side.  V3 was also traveling on the same roadway in the right lane.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.  This caused the frontal plane of V3 to impact the right side plane of V1.  Then the frontal planes of V3 and V1 impacted a parking meter pole and tree respectively located on the southern curb of this roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane five of a five lane controlled access roadway. V2 was traveling in lane four next to V1. A non-contact Medium-Heavy truck was traveling next to V2 in lane three when it began to change lanes to the left forcing V2 to also change lanes to the left. When changing lanes to the left the left side of V2's trailer contacted the right side of V1. This contact forced V1 to depart the roadway where the left side of V1 contacted a concrete barrier before continuing to travel forward across all five lanes to depart the roadway on the right, where the front of V1 contacted the guardrail face before coming to final rest.
Unit # 1 and unit #2 were both south bound in the #2 lane of a three-lane roadway. Unit # 2 stopped due traffic ahead. The front of unit #1 impacted the rear of unit # 2.

V2 and V3 were stopped facing westbound on a two lane undivided roadway.  V1 was traveling westbound on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back for V2, then the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.

V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway entering a five-legged intersection.  V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way roadway, entering the same sign controlled intersection as V2.  As V2 was traveling through the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 continued off the roadway before coming to final rest.
V1 was traveling northbound when a tree fell on to the hood.

V1 was traveling on a roadway heading north.  V2 was pulling out of a business driveway heading west, attempting to turn left.  V2's view was obstructed by another vehicle while pulling out into the roadway.  The front of V2 contacted the right of V1.  V1 then spun clockwise and came to final rest facing south in a business driveway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on roadway attempting to crossover an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound on roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was eastbound when the driver lost control and departed the roadway to the right side. V1 impacted a utility pole with its front right. The vehicle continued off the roadway where its front left struck a second utility pole and came to final rest.
V1 was stopped in the roadway, attempting to make a U-turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling in the same direction as V1, approaching the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.

Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling westbound on a four lane divided highway. Vehicle #1 traveling in lane one crossed over the lane line coming in contact with vehicle #2 traveling in lane two. V1 and V2 traveling westbound in the same lane. V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's rear plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south and vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same road. V1 pulled into a two-way left turn lane and came to a stop waiting to turn into a parking lot. When the parking lot was clear, V1 began to turn left and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #1 was south in lane one a two lane divided roadway. V1 traveled to its right to avoid a cow in the roadway. V1 began to rotate clockwise and traveled off the west road edge. The right rear side of V1 contacted a concrete drain and embankment. V1 then rolled on the right side leading ten quarter turns, ejecting the driver.

V1 was traveling west on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  V2 was traveling north in the left lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a a two-lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V2 was traveling south in front of V1 and stopped to make a left turn into a driveway. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling in opposite directions on the same two lane non divided roadway. V1 left its lane of travel to the left, and impacted the front of V2's frontal plane with its frontal plane.
V1 was negotiating a left curve when it lost control.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway with the right side of V1 contacting a road sign before coming to a final rest.

began to pass through the intersection and was contacted by unit 1.  Unit 1 then went off the right side of the road, contacted a traffic sign and a phone box before coming to final rest in the right of way.

V1 was traveling behind V2 heading eastbound when V2 slowed for traffic.  As a result the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane contacted a utility pole.  V1 then continued forward going down an embankment where the front plane contacted a large tree.  V1 then rotated clockwise around the tree where the left plane contacted another tree.

V1 was traveling north through the intersection.  V2 was traveling east through the intersection.  The front plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, four lane undivided roadway crossing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane divided roadway approaching the intersection that V1 was traveling through. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.
V1 traveling south crossing through intersection. Upon crossing intersection V1 departs lane left and contacts curb then a concrete wall off of roadway before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection in lane four. V2 was traveling southbound in lane three behind V1. V1 changed lanes to it's right into lane three. The front plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1.

V1 was headed eastbound on the roadway when it departed the roadway to the right. V1 struck the guardrail (RBC) then proceeded down the hill where the left rear bumper (undercarriage) struck the ground causing it to be partially separated. V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway with a center median divider. V1 traveled to its left and departed the west road edge. The front of V1 contacted a sign post. V1 continued to travel northwest and the front of V1 contacted the ditch dividing the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a left hand curve. V2 was negotiating a right hand curve. V1 departed the lane on the left side. V2 departed the lane on the left side. V1 (left front) and V2 (left front) collided and came to final rest in an unknown location
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a large tree branch in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound and was attempting to turn north bound at the intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound. V1 proceeded to turn northbound and was impacted on the back right side by the right front bumper of V2.
V1 was traveling west through an intersection. V2 was traveling south through the same intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound and V2 was traveling southbound; both approaching the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front end of V1 came into contact with the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling eastbound to southbound through a right hand turn at an intersection when it departed the roadway on the left and came into contact with a fire hydrant and shrubbery.

V1 was traveling Westbound on a two lane, two way roadway. Westbound V1 attempted to pass another vehicle, then swerved sharply to avoid a vehicle approaching from the opposite direction.  V1 entered a clockwise rotation and rolled to the left four quarter turns, coming to rest on its wheels, facing East.

V1 departed the right side of a two-lane roadway with traffic in opposite direction just before a bridge spanning a section of railway tracks. V1 rolled down an embankment and came to rest on its right side.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane non-divided roadway. V1 left the roadway to the right and impacted a utility pole with its left side. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and continued down an embankment, where V1 rolled over. Final rest V1 was sitting on its right side.

V2 was traveling westbound and was stopped prior to the intersection.  V1 was traveling from northbound to eastbound through a right hand turn.  The front end and the left side of V1 came into contact with the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound in the 2nd of two lanes. The driver lost directional control of the vehicle. V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The left side of V1 contacted the raised curb north of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling East exiting a parking lot attempting to turn left. Vehicle #2 was traveling South on a five lane two way roadway. V1 began to turn left and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in the center lane of a divided roadway with three lanes of travel in each direction.  On this roadway, V1 lost control and contacted with its right side plane a concrete wall inside of a highway overpass and then a wooden guardrail.

V1 was negotiating a left hand curve on a two-lane-undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, ascended an embankment, and rolled one quarter turn onto its left side coming to final rest in its original lane of travel.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 on the interstate. V1 steered to the right while braking when a deer entered onto the roadway. The deer impacted V1 on the left side.
V1 drove off the left side of a highway on ramp.  The vehicle's left side made contact with a ditch and then contacted the front end with a road sign,

V2 was stopped, at an intersection, facing westbound in lane 2 of a 5-lane undivided roadway.  V1 was traveling westbound on the same roadway, in the same lane.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a one-way, one-lane, curved right roadway. V2 came to a stop for traffic ahead of it. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V1.

V1 and V2 traveling east on roadway. V1's front plane contacted the rear of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in the first of four lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound in the second lane. V1 departed the lane on the left side and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and struck a mail box and the front plane struck a tree. V1 then rolled and contacted several trees during the roll and came to final rest on its top.

V1 impacted a metal light pole with the right plane. After impact to the pole, V1 entered a counter-clockwise yaw and impacted a guardrail end with the right plane and the a second metal light pole, also with the right plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.
V1 was heading south through an intersection as V2 was turning left. V1 front impacted the right side of V2. V2 then contacted a street sign with the left side.

V1 and V2 were traveling north bound on the same two lane one way roadway. V1 slowed to miss impact with a deer which entered the roadway from the right. V2's front contacted V1's rear plane. V1 then impacted the west side guard rail with its front. V1 spun in a counter clockwise rotation and impacted the west side guard rail with its rear plane.  V2 impacted the east side guard rail with its front.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersecting roadway to the south. V1 was behind V2. V2 slowed to turn left at the intersecting roadway and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were southbound in the middle lane of a two way roadway, approaching a rotary. V2 was stopped for traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a physically divided two-way roadway with three lanes of travel in each direction.  On this roadway, V1 lost control of vehicle and contacted the center median barrier with its left side plane.

V1, V2 & V3 were all traveling eastbound on a physically divided roadway with three lanes of travel in each direction. V1 was in lane #2, V2 was in lane #1 and V3 was in lane #3.  V1 changed lanes to the right as V2 changed lanes to the left. V1 and V2 contacted each other.  This caused V1 to spin counterclockwise and contact V3's right side plane.

V2 was traveling East on a 2 lane roadway with traffic divided by a left turn lane. V1 was traveling West on the same road with the intention of making a left turn. As V1 made the left turn, the front of V2 collided with the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were stopped at the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling east bound in lane 3 of 3. V2 was traveling west bound in lane 1 of 2. V1 attempted a left turn across 2 lanes. When this turn was attempted the front of V2 came into contact with the front of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling West, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling East, approaching the same intersection. V2 entered the intersection and began to turn left. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound in the first of two lanes. Vehicle 2 was stopped eastbound in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in lane No. 3 of a four-lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was also traveling westbound in lane No. 1. The driver of V1 lost directional control of the vehicle and departed lane No. 3, traversed lane No. 2 and entered lane No. 1  The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Vehicle 1 rotated CCW as the right side of Vehicle 1 impacted the left side of V2 in a secondary side-slap configuration.
V1 and V2 were traveling in the same direction in the same lane. V1's front contacted V2's rear.
V1 and V2 were initially traveling in opposite directions. V1 made a left turn across V2's path. V1's right side contacted V2's front.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound in lane 3 of a 3 lane southbound roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side, continued to travel south off the road for approximately 125 meters where it contacted a tree with its right side and a tree with its front in quick succession, and then immediately came to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on the roadway, while Vehicle 2 was headed northbound on the roadway.  As both vehicles were approaching an intersection, Vehicle 1 initiated a left turn to begin heading east.  The front end of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1 in the intersection.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest just off the edge of the pavement on the northeast corner of the intersection while Vehicle 2 came to final rest in the northeast portion of the intersection.
V1 and V2 were traveling East in the right turn lane of a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection and on ramp.  The front end of V2 contacted the rear end of V1.
V1 was traveling east through an intersection on a four lane, one way roadway.  V2 was traveling northbound through the same intersection on a four lane, one way roadway.

V1 was traveling in lane two of a four lane, two way divided by a grassy median roadway. V1 began to pass in the right lane, a vehicle that was traveling ahead of it in the same lane. During V1's attempt to pass the vehicle, V1 lost control and exited the roadway to the left and entered the grassy median in a counter-clockwise yaw where the right side of V1 contacted and sheared off a tree; before exiting the median in a clockwise yaw across the travel lanes opposite his original travel.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. Vehicle #2 was stopped at an intersection facing east. V1 impacted the front bumper on the back of V2.

The driver of Vehicle 2 was northbound and stopped for a traffic signal at a four-leg intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling north approaching the same intersection and the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the rear plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were stopped at the intersection in the lane to the left of V1's lane of travel. V4 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. V1 departed it's lane of travel to the left. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and impacted the rear of V3 with its front. V2 kept moving and entered the oncoming lanes of traffic. The front of V2 impacted the front of V4.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 2 of a 4 lane physically divided roadway.  V2 was stopped in lane 2 of the same roadway due to a previous crash (frontal damage).  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-way, two lane, roadway.  V2 was traveling behind V1 on the same roadway.  V2 stopped to turn into her driveway and the front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound. Vehicle #2 was traveling east bound. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 impacted the front on the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane frontage road in lane two. V2 was traveling eastbound on the exit ramp to the frontage road. As V2 attempted to merge into lane two of the frontage road the front V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 then lost control and departed the roadway to the south. The front of V1 contacted a chain link fence, V1 continued through the fence. The front of V1 contacted a parked trailer in a trucking yard.
V2 was traveling south through an intersection. V1 was traveling east through same intersection making a right hand turn. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2.
V1 was northbound on a two lane roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its front.

V1 was traveling East in the lane one. V1 cross over the center line to the left in a northeastern direction, cutting across the entire roadway and riding up onto the sidewalk on the north side of the road. The front plane of the vehicle impacted a tree and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of 5 lane highway. V2 was traveling the same direction in lane 2. V3 was traveling in the same direction as V1 and V2 in lane 3. V1 attempted to change lanes from lane 1 to lane 2. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact V1 departed the roadway and contacted a concrete barrier. V2 began to rotate counter clockwise, and the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V3.
V1 was traveling northbound attempting to make a left hand turn to continue west. V2 was traveling southbound through the same intersection. The front end of V1 impacted the front left of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 2-lane, 2-way, undivided roadway attempting to negotiate a left curve.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a <10cm steel post, then the front of V1 contacted a >10cm wood sign post.  That signs posts broke and the sign, fell and contacted the windshield, roof and backlight.  Then the front of V1 contacted a cluster of trees >10cm and a <10cm sign post.

V1 & V2 were heading southbound. The front passenger corner of V1 impacted the rear driver corner of V2. After impact, the driver of V1 attempted to flee and drove roughly 900 ft and attempted a right turn where they lost control and impacted a brick retaining wall.

V2 was stopped facing south on a two lane roadway at a 4 way intersection attempting to turn left to travel east. V1 was traveling southbound approaching V2 and the front plane of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 was Southbound on a city street. V2 was Eastbound on an intersecting city street. The front of V1 struck the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 8 lane not physically divided roadway passing through the intersection of a 4 lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane 1 passing through the same intersection when the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a four lane divided road.  V1 ran off the right side of the road striking the curb, V1's right side then struck a guard rail.  V1's left side then struck a utility pole and the front of V1 struck another utility pole.
V1 and V2 were headed northbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 struck the back of a trailer following V2.
V1 was turning southbound on a three-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane divided roadway. Front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in an intersection.

V1 was traveling west bound in lane 2 of 3 into an intersection where they attempted to turn south bound. V2 was traveling north bound in lane 1 of 4. V3 was traveling north bound in lane 3 of 4. The impact then cause V1 to cross traffic lanes where the front of V1 came into contact with the right of V3.

V1 was Northbound on a two lane, two way city street, approaching a T-Intersection. V1 entered the intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was Eastbound on the intersection road which is a two lane, two way city street. The front of V2 struck the front of V1.
V1 was traveling eastbound on an undivided roadway. The vehicle departed the roadway to the right, its front end coming into contact with a utility pole.

V1 was traveling southbound.  V2 entered the roadway from a driveway and was traveling from eastbound to northbound.  In that intersection, the front end of V1 came into contact with the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling north bound in lane 3 of 4. V2 was traveling north bound in lane 2 of 4. V1 departed travel lane on the right side. The front of V1 then came into contact with rear of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped southbound in the same lane ahead of V1. Vehicle 3 was stopped southbound in the same lane ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.
Vehicle #2 was stopped facing South in a two-way left turn lane. Vehicle #1 was traveling West and turned left into the two-way left turn lane. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west. Vehicle #2 was traveling east. V2 began to turn left at a driveway, and the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling northeast approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left and the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on an intersecting road.  Both vehicles entered the uncontrolled intersection, the front of V1 contacting the left of V2.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an object in the road.  V1 lost control and departed its lane to the right.  The front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the back of V2 contacted the left of V1.  V1 departed the road and the right of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane roadway in lane 2.  V2 was entering the roadway from an off ramp intending to travel southbound.  V2 made a U-turn in front of V1 intending to head northbound, causing the front of V1 to contact the left side of V2 twice.
Vehicle 1 was exiting a private business drive turning left (east) and Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane 1 when the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the left side of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane, one-way roadway rounding a curve to the right. V1 left the roadway to the right and V1's front end contacted a small retaining wall. V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane roadway when it went through a dip in the road. V1 traveled past the dip and V1's front end contacted the roadway. During the rollover the driver of V1 was ejected.
V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane two of a divided roadway, V1 behind V2. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way undivided roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction and a parking lane. V2 was parked and unoccupied facing southbound on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the left lane of a two-way roadway turning left (north) into a driveway. V2 was traveling westbound in the left lane of the same roadway.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1.

V1 was traveling south through a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling east through the same intersection. The front of V2 collided with the right side of V1. V1 subsequently overturned an unknown number of times.

V1 was traveling on a rural 2 lane roadway. V1 left the roadway to the right, where it impacted the embankment with its frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise and impacted several small trees, the ground and a large tree with its left plane. V1 also impacted a small tree with its frontal plane before before coming to final rest.

Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling north, in the same lane. V3 stopped for traffic, V2 , behind V3, slowed, and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2, then the front of V2 impacted the back of V3.
V1 was traveling South on a 2 lane rural road with traffic traveling in the opposite direction. V1 departed the road to the left, collided with a ditch and came to rest against a culvert.
Vehicle 1 was traveling on a congested freeway system.  The driver of vehicle 1 looked back to see if it was clear to change lanes. It was at this point that the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in lane 1 of a two lane roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound in lane 2 of a two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 made a left turn into the eastbound roadway. Vehicle 1 (right) collided with vehicle 2 (front). Vehicle 2 came to final rest in the roadway.  Vehicle 1 then rotated clockwise while traveling forward and struck a wooden fence with its frontal plane.
V1 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of a two lane roadway.  V1 ran off the right side of the roadway.  V1's frontal plane struck a utility pole.
V1 and V2 were both traveling eastbound at a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane.

V2 traveling south on roadway. V1 headed eastbound approaching from adjacent street to non controlled intersection. V1 stops at stop sign and turns left onto roadway. V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's frontal plane.

V1 was approaching an intersection heading northbound. V2 was traveling southbound toward the same intersection. V3 stopped at the intersection facing east. V1 turned westbound at the intersection. The right side of V1 then contacted the front of V3. V1 continued southbound and departed the roadway. The front of V1 then contacted a fire hydrant. V1 continued through the fire hydrant. The front of V1 then contacted a wooden utility pole.

V1 and V2 were traveling East in lane 1 of a two-way divided roadway approaching an intersection.  V1 was attempting to turn left while V2 was attempting to overtake V1.  The right side of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two way roadway.  V1 crossed the center line to the northbound side. V1 continued traveling southbound, exiting the roadway.  The front of the vehicle made contact with a utility pole on the northbound side of the roadway.  V1 came to final rest on the shoulder, facing southbound.

V1 was traveling South in lane two of a two-way undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway into a ditch and rolled over for 8 quarter turns before coming to a final rest on its wheels.

V1 traveling westbound on a divided, two lane roadway. The vehicle departed the right side of the roadway, impacting a curb with its right front wheel/rim (Event 1) and then a fire hydrant with its frontal plane (Event 2). V1 drove an unknown distance before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway.  V2 was behind V3 and were stopped in traffic ahead of V1 on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back for V2.  V1 came to rest off the right side of the roadway.  After initial contact, V2 rotated counterclockwise and the right side of V2 contacted the back of V3.  After contact with V3, V2 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V2 contacted a rock.

V1, V2, and V3 were approaching the same 4 way intersection. V3 was pending a left turn in the northbound lanes. The front of V1 entered the intersection from the eastbound lanes and impacted with right front of V2 that was coming from the southbound lanes. V2 then departed the roadway to the left and impacted with a bush line which became its final rest position. V1 rotated clockwise and the front impacted with the front of V3.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 5 lane one way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane one way roadway approaching the intersection.  The front of V2 struck the left rear tire of V2 causing V2 to rotate counterclockwise where it continued southbound departing the roadway.  As a result of departing the roadway the front of V2 struck a guardrail end and again on the right rear side.  V2 came to final rest with the front striking a large concrete decorative pillar facing south.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane roadway.  There was a boat on a trailer parked on the right side of the road.  The front of V1 contacted the back of the boat and trailer.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 started to rotate counter clockwise, and V2 started to rotate clockwise. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 again in a side slap impact.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound. Vehicle #2 was traveling south bound. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 front contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was eastbound on a 2 lane roadway. V1 turned left and departed the lane and then the roadway to the left. The right side of V1 impacted with a stop sign.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an unlit two lane, two way country road. V1 departed the roadway to the right side where it contacted a tree with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling southbound and attempted to turn right into a private drive. V1 left the roadway on the right side traveling down small embankment striking a ditch on the frontal plane and coming to final rest.

V1 driving south on interstate departed left side of roadway. V1 continued into a median/ditch where V1 initiated rollover. V1 rolled left longitudinally approximately 9 quarter turns, struck a light pole with left side, and came to final rest in the median.

V1 was traveling eastbound at an intersection attempting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling southbound approaching the same intersection. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The vehicles then side slapped with V1's left plane contacting V2's right plane.

V1 was traveling south bound in lane 4 of 4. V2 was traveling south bound in lane 2 of 4. V1 lost control and started to spin clockwise. When this happened the right of V1 came into contact with the front of V2. After first contact both V1  then rotated counterclockwise and V2 rotated clockwise where they then side slapped and made a secondary contact. V2 then traveled west bound off of roadway where it then came into contact with a guard rail on the right side.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling westbound.  V3 was ahead of V2, and V2 was ahead of V1.  As V3 slowed in response to traffic conditions, and as V2 slowed in response to V3, the front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.  The front end of V2 then came into contact with the back end of V3.
V2 was Northbound in lane 1 of a 5 lane road. V2 stopped in traffic. V1 was on the same road behind V2. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane two-way roadway. Medical condition occurred causing the driver to depart the roadway. The front of V1 contacted a gas line marker and then the undercarriage contacted a culvert. V1 wheels left the driving surface, crossing over another roadway. Once landed, V1 turned southbound off of the roadway where the front of V1 contacted a fence with its front before coming to final rest in a field.

V1 was heading northbound changing lanes from lane 1 to lane 2 on a roadway separated by a center median with shrubs and trees. V2 was heading southbound in lane 2 on the other side of the median. V1 departed the left side of the roadway. An unknown plane of V1 impacted the curb. V1 traveled across the median with an unknown plane impacting shrubbery and a 33cm tree. At some point during the crash events an unknown direction rollover was initiated as V1 traveled into the southbound lanes. An unknown plane of V1 impacted the top of V2 and came to rest on its wheels behind V2 facing south.
V1 was traveling northbound when it departed the roadway on the left.  Its front end then came into contact with a curb, a chain link fence, and a culvert.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north as the road curved left. V1 departed the road to the right and the right side of V1 contacted a telephone pole. The front end of V1 contacted two small trees. The left side of V1 contacted a tree, then the front end of V1 contacted a barbed wire fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North, negotiating a left curve in the road. V1 departed the road to the right and entered a downward sloping soft gravel embankment. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise and the right plane contacted a tree. As a result, V1 began to rotate counterclockwise sharply. The front plane of V1 contacted a tree, then the back plane of V1 contacted another tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 then rotated 2 1/4 turns counter-clockwise to the NW where it contacted a stop sign and a tree where it came to rest. V2 rotated 3 1/4 turns clockwise as it also traveled to the NW, down a steep embankment. V2 rolled over, contacted a barbed wire fence and came to rest in a pond.
Vehicle one and vehicle two were traveling westbound in the right lane. Vehicle one began to slow down for traffic. Vehicle two braked and impacted the rear of vehicle one.
V1 was traveling southbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in the number one lane.  V1 ran off the right side of the road and struck two signs and a tree.

Vehicle 2 turned left out of a driveway into the left turn lane of a five lane roadway heading east. Vehicle 2 changed lanes just prior to an intersection and proceeded into the intersection.  V1 was westbound on the roadway and turned left at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling West.  Vehicle #2 was traveling East on the same trafficway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the road to the left.  The back and left planes of V1 contacted light poles.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane divided roadway in the number 2 lane.  V2 was traveling eastbound on the same four lane divided roadway in the number 1 lane.  V1 was attempting to initiate a right turn into a private parking lot.  V2's frontal plane struck the right rear side of V2 causing it to rotate clockwise.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on the 2 lane undivided roadway.  As the vehicle was passing over a bridge a deer began crossing the road from the north to the south.  Vehicle 1 made contact with the deer on the bridge where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was legally parked on the south curb right before the intersection. The driver of V2 was about to exit the vehicle. Before reaching the intersection V1 changed into the lane to its right. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the third lane on a two way undivided roadway with three lanes of travel in the northbound direction and two lanes of travel in the southbound direction. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway in the second lane with two lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 was making a left turn at the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2.
V1 traveling EB and failed to stop at stop sign. V2 traveling NB and turning left to head WB after stopping at the stop sign. The front end of V1 contacted left side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction, attempting to turn left heading northbound.  V2 was traveling southbound in lane 2 of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1.
V1 and V2 were both traveling in the left lane of a one-way roadway with three lanes of travel and an entrance ramp lane.  On this roadway, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane roadway with traffic in opposite directions. While negotiating a left curve V1 departed the right side of the roadway and struck a rocky hillside. V1 overturned 4 quarter turns and came to final rest facing south in the southbound lane of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the left and Vehicle #2 was traveling south, negotiating a curve to the right; both vehicles were in the same travel lane. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact to V1, the right side of V2 impacted a concrete wall.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway.  V1 was approaching a left hand curve when it departed the road on the right side.  V1 continued to travel off the road where the front plane struck a wooden fence followed by a large tree.

Vehicle 1 was headed eastbound on a 4 lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was westbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 began the process of a left turn into a parking lot and made contact to Vehicle 2's front end with its right side.  The force of the impact caused Vehicle 1 to rotate clockwise while moving left where it struck a concrete sign in the parking lot with its left side.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest at the concrete sign and Vehicle 2 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the turn lane of a two-way undivided roadway with left turn lane approaching an intersection, intending to make a left turn.  V2 was was traveling in the opposite direction in lane 1 passing through the same intersection.  The front end of V2 contacted the front end of V1.
Vehicle 1 was headed westbound on the 2 lane undivided roadway.  A deer entered the road from the North side and made contact with the front end of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling westbound toward a four way intersection in lane 2. V2 was stopped in lane 2, at the same intersection facing westbound. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 while approaching the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a major highway. V2 was traveling on the same highway in the same lane ahead of V1. V1 changed into the lane to its right in order to overtake V2. V1 moved back into lane three ahead of V2. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V2 moved to the left and impacted a concrete traffic barrier with its front. V2 partially climbed onto the concrete barrier and moved partially on top of the barrier before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a three lane highway. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same highway. Both vehicle's were traveling in the first lane. As traffic slowed the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a 4-lane non-divided roadway approaching stopped traffic, the front of V1 struck the rear of V2.
Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound. V2's front bumper impacted a deer that that had entered the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both travelling south on a two lane two-way traffic road. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V1 spun clockwise and was again struck by the front of V2 on the right side. V1 and V2 then impacted the guardrail and came to rest in the road.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and impacted the front bumper on the cable barrier and also impacting the Left side on the cable barrier.

V1 was traveling northbound negotiating a left curve. An animal entered the roadway and the driver steered right to avoid the animal. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a guard rail. A sign was contacted by an unknown plane then V1 re entered the roadway. V1 crossed over both lanes and departed the left road edge and the front plane contacted a guard rail.

V1 was northbound in lane three attempting to turn left at an intersection. V2 traveling southbound in lane two entering the same intersection as V1. In the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was eastbound of a 3 lane roadway approaching a 5 way intersection. V2 and V3 were southbound approaching same intersection. V4 was northbound approaching same intersection. The left side of V1 impacted with the front of V2. V1's right side then impacted with the front of V3. The front of V1 impacted with the left of V4.
V1 was traveling north approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east approaching the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on an undivided roadway approaching the intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on an undivided roadway, attempting to make a left hand turn to continue south. The front end of V2 contacted the front right side of V1.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  A deer entered the roadway from the north edge, and the front of V1 contacted the deer.
V1 was traveling east on a two-lane roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway.  The front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2.

V1 rolled over left to top down an embankment and came to rest on it's top.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane undivided roadway. V1 crossed over the center line to the left, then departed the roadway to the left before striking a utility pole with its frontal plane.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were stopped at an intersection heading west on a two way, two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 front made contact with Vehicle 2 rear in the process of navigating on-coming traffic from the south.

V1 was traveling westbound and V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left, and its front end came into contact with the front end of V2 (event 1).  V1 rotated in a clockwise direction, and its left rear wheel/tire came into contact with a curb (event 2).

V1 and V2 were both traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway through a construction zone. The left front of V1 impacted with the left side of V2. V1 departed the lane to the left and impacted with the traffic attenuator. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest next to a utility pole.

V2 was traveling North in lane 2 of a divided highway. V1 was traveling South on the same roadway. V1, intending to make a left turn entered the intersection where the front of V1 collided with the front of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection and Vehicle #2 was traveling north, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight, and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V2 traveled thru the intersection in an Easterly direction and it's front contacted the left side of V1 which was heading in a northerly direction. V1's right side then contacted the left side of V3 which was also heading in a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling in the Number 2 lane of a southbound two-lane restricted access roadway. As V1 approached the entrance to an exit ramp it moved from the Number 2 lane to the Number 1 lane of the roadway. V2 was traveling in the Number 1 lane of the roadway and the front of V2 collided with the back of V1.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling east, on a divided highway, in adjacent lanes. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
Unit 1 was westbound when the left side was struck by a tire lost by a non-contact vehicle.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection and Vehicle #2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.
